1. Install Node.js (if not already installed):
   - Option 1: Install via package manager (e.g., on Ubuntu: \`sudo apt install nodejs npm\`)
   - Option 2: Download from official Node.js website

2. Install nvm (Node Version Manager) for Linux:
   - Run: \`curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash\`
   - Exit and reopen terminal

3. Install specific Node.js version (optional):
   - \`nvm install 20.16\`
   - \`nvm use 20.16\`

4. Install SASS globally:
   - \`npm install -g sass@3.7.4\`

5. Verify installation:
   - \`sass --version\` should show 3.7.4

Alternative installation methods:
- For Windows/Mac: Download Dart Sass from https://sass-lang.com/install
- For other package managers:
  - yarn: \`yarn global add sass@3.7.4\`
  - pnpm: \`pnpm add -g sass@3.7.4\`" > 0-installation-script